<Base title="About">
  <h1>About Toronto Micro-Atlas</h1>

  <p>Toronto Micro-Atlas is an independent web publication of Field Guides about noticing Toronto. Each guide maps a set of located observations: places where something specific is happening with the landscape, the infrastructure, or the city's relationship to its own topography.</p>

  <p>The guides are written from direct observation. Sources are cited. Nothing is reviewed; things are described.</p>

  <section>
    <h2>Field Guide 01: Hidden Landscapes</h2>
    <p>An interactive illustrated map of eight threshold locations (ravines, bridges, stair descents, underpasses, and trail entrances) where Toronto steps through a gap in its own surface into something older.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Made by</h2>
    <p>Jonathan Westberry. Toronto.</p>
  </section>
</Base>
